      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUICK THINKIN' (1) has missed the placings at his last couple but was in the money three back when third (29.80) at Nowra in a Grade 4/5. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. STOMP SHUFFLE (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 520m behind Money Keeping (30.86) in a Grade 5. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. One of the better hopes. ZIPPING BILPIN (3) was out of the placings last time when sixth at this track (30.34) but scored four back at this track (30.07). Form here at this distance is sound. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Has ability and can atone. NOT OUR FAULT (4) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
